('RET-LIT-001', 'Litigation Hold — All Documents', 'When litigation is reasonably anticipated, all potentially relevant documents must be preserved regardless of normal retention schedules until the hold is lifted.', '["OTHER"]', 0, 0, 'PERMANENT', 'LITIGATION_HOLD', 'FRCP Rule 37(e); Zubulake v. UBS Warburg; Cal. CCP § 2023.010 (misuse of discovery)', 'FEDERAL', '["LITIGATION_READINESS","EVIDENTIARY","LEGAL_COMPLIANCE"]', '["DIGITAL_WITH_AUDIT_TRAIL","TAMPER_EVIDENT"]', 'NO_DESTRUCTION', '"ALL"', '"ALL"', 'Spoliation sanctions: adverse inference, issue preclusion, default judgment, contempt, monetary sanctions, criminal obstruction (18 USC § 1519)', 'Litigation hold overrides ALL other retention rules. Must be issued as soon as litigation is reasonably anticipated, not when complaint is filed.', 1, '1800-01-01', 'https://www.law.cornell.edu/rules/frcp/rule_37');
